articles.title: Live Coverage: SpaceX to launch 25 Starlink Satellites from the West Coast
articles.summary: Liftoff from Space Launch Complex 4 East is scheduled for 1:55:50 a.m. PST (4:55:50 a.m. EST / 0955:50 UTC). The rocket will take southerly trajectory on departure from the launch site in central California.

articles.title: Intuitive Machines raises $175 million in stock sale
articles.summary:
Intuitive Machines raised $175 million in a stock sale Feb. 25 and plans to use the proceeds to help build out a deep space communications network.
The post Intuitive Machines raises $175 million in stock sale appeared first on SpaceNews.

articles.title: Rocket Lab Showcases Hypersonic Test Flight
articles.summary: On February 27th, 2026, Rocket Lab launched the “That’s Not A Knife” mission from Wallops Island, Virginia, carrying a hypersonic test vehicle for the Defense Innovation Unit.

articles.title: NASA on ‘aggressive’ schedule to complete SLS repairs for April launch
articles.summary:
NASA has about three weeks to complete repairs to the Space Launch System’s upper stage to make the next launch window for the Artemis 2 mission in early April.
The post NASA on ‘aggressive’ schedule to complete SLS repairs for April launch appeared first on SpaceNews.
